/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 730.89 Tm (This section describes the currently implemented codebase as the practical realization of the dataset) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 719.09 Tm (methodology proposed in this thesis. The core idea is that humor data should not be treated as a flat) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 707.29 Tm (collection of isolated jokes. Instead, it should be transformed into a layered resource in which each joke) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 695.49 Tm (is connected to semantic representations, weak constraints, and multiple references. Such a representation) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 683.69 Tm (is better aligned with creative generation, where a single prompt may admit many acceptable outputs and) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 671.89 Tm (where exact lexical overlap is often a poor proxy for semantic relatedness.) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 656.09 Tm (The repository is therefore not merely an engineering scaffold. It operationalizes a research assumption:) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 644.29 Tm (before one can study reasoning-based humor generation, one needs a corpus that is both large and) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 632.49 Tm (semantically structured. The implemented pipeline moves from raw text collection to progressively richer) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 620.69 Tm (annotations, and each stage materializes a separate dataset. Methodologically, this is useful because it) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 608.89 Tm (makes the process reproducible, allows each representation layer to be inspected independently, and avoids) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 597.09 Tm (collapsing the whole construction problem into a single brittle model call.) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 581.29 Tm (A second motivation behind the current design is epistemic caution. In humor research, many desirable labels) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 569.49 Tm (are difficult to define sharply and even harder to annotate consistently at scale. It is therefore) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 557.69 Tm (advantageous to build supervision gradually. Dense embeddings, sparse keywords, and retrieved references are) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 545.89 Tm (not final ground truth in the strict sense, but they are informative intermediate objects that can support) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 534.09 Tm (later training and analysis. The implemented code should thus be read as a pipeline for constructing) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 522.29 Tm (increasingly informative approximations to the latent structure of humorous texts.) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 506.49 Tm (This staged methodology also matches the broader argument of the thesis. The long-term objective is not) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 494.69 Tm (simply to store jokes, but to organize them in a way that supports reasoning-oriented generation and) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 482.89 Tm (learning without relying on a single verifier. For such a setting, the corpus must expose relations between) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 471.09 Tm (jokes: topical proximity, shared constraints, and families of plausible reference answers. The existing code) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 459.29 Tm (already moves in this direction by turning a raw corpus into a set of linked semantic views.) Tj
/F2 13.00 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 439.49 Tm (Dataset Construction Strategy) Tj
/F2 10.50 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 422.49 Tm (Corpus-first design.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 409.49 Tm (The implemented pipeline begins with large externally available joke corpora rather than with manually) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 397.69 Tm (authored prompts. This reflects a methodological trade-off: if the objective is to construct a resource with) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 385.89 Tm (diverse humor mechanisms, broad topical coverage, and many potential reference answers, then naturally) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 374.09 Tm (occurring joke collections are preferable to small curated prompt-response datasets. They contain recurring) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 362.29 Tm (topics, repeated lexical cues, and stylistic variation that later make multi-reference supervision possible.) Tj
/F2 10.50 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 346.49 Tm (Source selection and complementarity.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 333.49 Tm (The current code uses two fixed sources: the Short Jokes corpus and the rJokes corpus. Their combination is) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 321.69 Tm (methodologically attractive because it balances short one-liners with more heterogeneous community-style) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 309.89 Tm (jokes. The first source contributes brevity, lexical compactness, and many formulaic punchline patterns. The) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 298.09 Tm (second contributes broader topical diversity, looser discourse structure, and a wider range of) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 286.29 Tm (community-generated humor forms. Using both sources is therefore a way of reducing dependence on a single) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 274.49 Tm (stylistic regime.) Tj
/F2 10.50 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 258.69 Tm (Reproducibility and frozen acquisition.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 245.69 Tm (The sources are downloaded from pinned GitHub commits rather than mutable endpoints, so the acquisition) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 233.89 Tm (process remains stable across runs. This detail matters methodologically because later analysis of retrieval) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 222.09 Tm (quality, prompt construction, or training behavior should not be confounded by silent changes in the) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 210.29 Tm (underlying corpus. Freezing acquisition reduces dataset drift and supports later comparison and ablation) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 198.49 Tm (studies.) Tj
/F2 10.50 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 182.69 Tm (Canonicalization and provenance preservation.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 169.69 Tm (After acquisition, the raw files are normalized into a shared parquet representation with a unified global) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 157.89 Tm (identifier, while source metadata are preserved. This reflects the methodological principle that) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 146.09 Tm (heterogeneous corpora should be merged without erasing provenance. Retaining source information makes it) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 134.29 Tm (possible to inspect domain effects, identify source-specific artifacts, or later perform filtering and) Tj
1 0 0 1 64.00 122.49 Tm (balancing, while the global identifier becomes the stable key for all downstream annotations.) Tj
/F2 10.50 Tf
1 0 0 1 64.00 106.69 Tm (Minimal normalization and noise tolerance.) Tj
/F1 9.00 Tf
1 0 0 1 295.16 30.00 Tm (1) Tj
